Study

EKS = AWS-managed control plane. You manage nodes (managed node groups, self-managed, or Fargate).
IRSA (IAM Roles for Service Accounts) — OIDC-based pod-level AWS permissions.
AWS Load Balancer Controller — provisions ALB/NLB from Ingress/Service.
VPC CNI for pod networking; pods get VPC IPs.
Hands-On

eksctl create cluster --name dev --region us-east-1 --nodes 2
aws eks update-kubeconfig --name dev --region us-east-1
kubectl get nodes

# Enable IRSA
eksctl utils associate-iam-oidc-provider --cluster dev --approve
eksctl create iamserviceaccount --cluster dev --name s3-reader \
  --attach-policy-arn arn:aws:iam::aws:policy/AmazonS3ReadOnlyAccess --approve

# Install AWS LB Controller via helm (per AWS docs)

